{
  "root_cause": "When SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE is False (the default), the CudaIpcTensorTransportProxy is created with pool_ipc_handle=None, forcing the non-pooled IPC path. In this path, torch.UntypedStorage._new_shared_cuda(*redirected_handle) is called directly on a per-slice IPC handle that may have been invalidated if the sender's tensor buffer was freed or recycled before the receiver reconstructed the tensor. Under high concurrency (concurrency=128), multiple concurrent requests increase the likelihood of stale handles, causing HIP error: invalid device pointer. The non-pooled path also lacks a retry mechanism when a handle fails, whereas the pooled path has cache invalidation and retry logic.",
  "fix": "Set SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1 to enable the IPC pool handle cache. This causes the CudaIpcTensorTransportProxy to be created with pool_ipc_handle=pool._pool_ipc_handle (the pool's persistent CUDA IPC handle), which ensures the pooled IPC path is used. The pooled path keeps the pool storage persistently open and cached, so the handle always points to valid memory, and includes a cache invalidation retry mechanism when a stale handle is detected.",
  "evidence": "1) Crash log line 3713: '[TP1] Failed to deserialize from CUDA IPC handle (HIP error: invalid device pointer)' - the same error described in the task. 2) Crash log line 3644-3647: stacktrace shows 'File cuda_ipc_transport_utils.py, line 488, in reconstruct_on_target_device: storage = torch.UntypedStorage._new_shared_cuda(*redirected_handle) torch.AcceleratorError: HIP error: invalid device pointer' - unambiguously the non-pooled path. 3) Crash log line 736: 'MmItemMemoryPool has no free chunk large enough for a 67.50 MiB tensor (pool size: 1024.00 MiB); falling back to non-IPC transport' - demonstrates pool stress under concurrency. 4) environ.py line 718: 'SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE = EnvBool(False)' - the default is False, which triggers the non-pooled path causing the crash. 5) base_processor.py lines 1229-1232: 'pool_ipc_handle=(self.cudaipc_mmfeature_pool._pool_ipc_handle if _IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE else None)' - confirms the non-pooled path is selected when the flag is False."
}
